# ── Rsync duplicates (dual-package structure artefact) ────────────────────────
# The BGI Python package lives in bgi/bgi/ (the pip-installable package).
# Running `rsync bgi/bgi/*.py bgi/` creates duplicates at bgi/ and repo root.
# These duplicates are NEVER committed — they exist only to satisfy pytest imports.
#
# The following paths are rsync shadow copies — ignore them:
/cli.py
/pipeline.py
/__init__.py
/ai/
/core/
/delta/
/gate1/
/gate2/
/gate3/
/output/
/sep/
/telemetry.py
